When I woke up, I was in a place I didn't recognize.
I can't remember anything but my name. It seems that I have amnesia .......
On the other side was a young subhuman girl, Feste. She seemed to have taken a liking to us after we rescued her from the Goblins.
However, I wonder how it is that I was made her "servant" before I knew it. ......
The place where she met Feste is "a recently discovered ruin. There may be clues to her memory there.

It would be more convenient for me to become an Adventurer for the future.
Pass the exam and register as an Adventurer.

My life as an Adventurer has begun.
Accepting requests, meeting people, and traveling to different lands would naturally lead to a search for memories.
First of all, I decided to take on a good job that Jake had introduced me to.
I wonder what it will be like. ......

In "Dragon Claw Valley," he encountered the legendary monster Avaritia. In addition, a mysterious boy named Merluof, who descended from the Sky, told me the word "kurisha," which means "the coming one.
Are these related to lost memories?
I would like to find out more, but Feste refuses to listen to me, saying that he is going to the Coin Pavilion.
Because Jake blew him off and told him that the husband would buy him a drink. ......

I was able to speak with Priest Walkin and his disciple Milene of the Bapharia religion about the "Visitors.
The "Visitors" are gentiles with special powers.
The secret is said to lie in the "Pillar of Divinity," the greatest holy place of the Bapharian faith, which stands tall on the Bahamar Plateau.

In "Pillar of Divinity," I met Aerinse and Tyris, who came from 1000 years in the future.
They said they were going to liberate Avaritia and save the planet from the coming doom.
We agreed to cooperate with them.
Tyris has a favor to ask of us right away.

An anomalous reaction of engrams that appeared in the omnistron.
There is a strong possibility that it is Avaritia.
Let's cooperate with Aerinse and his team and succeed in liberating Avaritia.

A request from Coin Owner.
It seems to be a simple errand, but the item to be delivered seems to be a very bad product, "Once you get a taste of it, there's no going back.

Feste, who had been talking mysteriously with a stray cat, suddenly asked me to go and get some "Horn Goat meat.
This is also the role of a servant, so let's follow him without asking any questions.

A simple job of delivering a letter to the Priest of Minsterhorn.
However, there was a secret of Jake's hidden in there, which should not be touched.

The Coin Owner gave me a job for a reason, saying that he was originally going to ask someone else to do it.
I should be prepared to take some risks.

Tyris suddenly started asking questions of a boy he didn't recognize.
Did he get some important information ......?
His expression was full of impatience and determination.

Aerinse and Tyris are talking about something interesting.
We may be able to catch a glimpse of the secrets of these two enigmatic people from the future.

A snooty rich man offers you a job.
He says he wants to donate an expensive, rare, and beautiful item that will attract the interest of the oracle's priestess. ......

I received a letter of acceptance from Poirier and all the assignments were completed.
Huovi came in the middle of the assignment and started a quarrel with Poirier, but a pass is a pass.
Now I can register as an Adventurer.
Let's go and report to Mewry.

We found a very powerful monster deep in the Dragon Claw Valley and managed to Hunt it down.
According to Feste, this monster is "Avaritia," a being that lives beyond time and space.
Why does this monster, the monster of adventure tales, exist?
And who am I ...... to have Hunt it down?

Jake went to report to the Pioneer Bureau first, saying, "I have to warn people about Avaritia.
Just then, a boy descended from the Sky.
The boy, whose name was Merluof, left behind a mysterious tweet, "The Coming One.
What does this have to do with his memories?
Feste seemed to recognize the word, but he could not recall it.
For now, let's go back to the pioneer station and get Reward from Jake.

I rescued Walkin from a monster attack at the Giant Tower Ruins.
When I asked him about the "visitors," Walkin began to lay out his theory at a furious pace.
The "visitors" are gentiles with special powers, he said. They are also considered by some to be the bringers of misfortune.
Walkin claimed that the founder of the Bapharia cult was also a "visitor" from another world, and he was transferred to the left from the headquarters of the cult.
Walkin passionately argued that if one were to examine the "Pillar of Divinity," the most sacred site of the Bapharia cult, he would be able to find out more about the "visitors.
...... Anyway, Walkin was able to find it successfully.
I will report this to Milene in the village of Minsterhorn.

On the top floor of the Pillar of Divinity, Avaritia was sealed.
As they approached, a dazzling sphere of light suddenly appeared, and two girls appeared from inside. Avaritia was also unsealed and went berserk, attacking the girls.
Somehow, they managed to fight off Avaritia, but the girls' true identities were unknown. They were still under strong caution.
And then...
The walls of the room shattered, and a new intruder appeared.
Voldigen, the king of the largest and strongest dragon tribe.
His overwhelming power ate Avaritia, and even kicked out the elite Gatekeepers.
Voldigen set his sights on us and approached slowly.
There was no escape, no choice but to fight.
Just when we thought that, the girls created a sphere of light. We dove into the light as they called us.
When the light disappeared, Voldigen's figure suddenly disappeared and Avaritia, who was supposed to have defeated him, was sealed in the ceiling.
It was as if nothing had happened.

I asked the two girls what had happened.
Their names are Aerinse and Tyris. They said that they had escaped from Voldigen by jumping through time through "chronoleaping.
It is hard to believe, but when I was leaving the "Pillar of Divinity," I passed "Myself and Feste" coming in. ......
We saw ourselves in the past. I guess it means that they really jumped through time and went back to the past.
Aerinse looks distressed, perhaps from the effects of the chronoleap.
We decided to return to Larpal to calm down for the time being.

I got the parts Tyris asked for.
I'll get it to you as soon as I can.

It was also Avaritia who responded to the omnistron.
Aerinse performed the "Liberation Ceremony" for Avaritia, who was Hunt. Avaritia, enveloped in a solemn myriad of lights, disappeared as if guided by Aerinse.
Avalitia is a being that arises from the distortion of time and space by killing its past self. That is Avaritia.
Only Aerinse can correct the distortion and restore the twisted causality.
However, the ritual is also an act that wears Aerinse down.
We decided to return to Rietze once more to let Aerinse rest.

After returning from the Cliff Ruins, I spoke with Jake again, and he introduced me to Guidance Miss Mullie of the Pioneer Bureau.
As soon as she saw the "Imagine" we had obtained at the ruins, she recognized it as a "Goblin" Battle Imagine.
It was not particularly rare, but it was a lucky find.
To become an Adventurer, one must take an exam.
Mury will be in charge of the test, so I will hear more details from her.

I have completed the registration test and am now a fully-fledged Adventurer.
Now I can accept requests from the Pioneer Bureau. However, Mullie advised me to remember to raise my "Adventurer Rank" as well.
The higher your rank, the better you are as an Adventurer, the more you can Accept requests with higher Rewards and go to more dangerous places.
To raise your rank, you need to clear the "Adventure Board. The first one was received from Mury.
He also gave me a "Glory Coin (GC)" as a reward for Hunt at "Lakerid Mine.
The GC could be exchanged for various items at the "Souvenir Exchange.
Jake told me that if I became an Adventurer, he would give me a good job.
I would go see Jake and report back to him.

Jake gave me Reward for my request and some information of interest.
Recently, unidentified creatures have been sighted in many places. It is rumored to be Avaritia.
The time of the increase in sightings coincides with the beginning of the dragon tribe's rampage.
Jake will continue to follow up on this information.
Incidentally, the Coin Owner also offered to buy him a drink to celebrate the accomplishment of his request.
When Feste heard this, he changed the color of his eyes and said, "I'm going to the Coin Pavilion! and the color of his eyes changed.

Walkin and Milene started a heated discussion about "Giant Tower Ruins" and ancient civilizations as soon as they met each other.
He is ...... in good health, but he doesn't seem to be listening to our questions any more.
The secret of "The Visitor" may lie in the "Pillar of Divinity.
Let's go there next time.

Aerinse and Tyris have come from 1000 years in the future.
The purpose is to liberate Avaritia.
Avaritia distorts space-time just by existing, and the accumulated distortion will engulf this planet.
In the not-too-distant future, this planet and the world will be destroyed.
If the distortion is still small, it can be dealt with. For this reason, the two came to the present by means of chronoleap.
However, the chronoleap is a serious secret and must not be known to anyone.
Tyris, with his sword at his side, has given him a choice: "Cooperation or death.
To save the stars, there was no choice but to cooperate.
Both Aerinse and Tyris bowed their heads to our answer, as if they did not want to force us to do anything.
Thus, we helped Aerinse and Tyris liberate Avaritia.
It is worrisome that even Tyris signed the servants' agreement, being persuaded by Feste's mouthpiece. ......

While Tyris was repairing the omnistron, I talked with Aerinse.
It seems that people like them, who came to the city after chrono-leaping, were once called "visitors".
Aerinse said that she could understand the fluctuation of the engrams peculiar to the "visitors. However, she does not see any characteristics that would indicate that she is a "comer.
Was Merluof wrong?
When the repaired omnistron was activated, a response was seen in Montenol Valley.
Aerinse and Tyris are going ahead with a field survey. They also gave me a child omnistron for contact.

Tyris apologized and thanked me for what I had done up until the liberation of Avaritia.
It seems that in her own way, she had her share of heartache.
The liberation of Avaritia by Aerinse must continue in order to avoid a future of destruction.
However, even the Dragon King Voldigen stands in the way. According to Tyris, Voldigen is also an Avaritia, and he is enhancing his power by feeding on other Avaritia.
If Avaritia is not freed before Voldigen, the planet will still be destroyed by Voldigen, who has taken in its power and distortions.
In order to protect the world and save the future, he promised again to lend his strength to Aerinse and Tyris.

First of all, let's say hello to the owner of this inn.
Let's go to the counter on the first floor.

Feste seems to be a familiar face with the "Two-Faced Coin Owner".
And it seems that the bill for the lodging is piling up. ......
The owner advised him to be properly prepared if he was going to leave town.

The name of the city is Asterleeds.
It is said to be the largest trading city on the Magna continent. Buildings line the streets and the streets are crowded with people.
The streets are crowded with people.
It really is a big city.
First of all, let's go to the "Town Gate Square" at the entrance of the city.

A huge transfer portal is placed at the town gate square.
Using this, they can get back to the city immediately.
Touch the portal to register.

The transfer portal at the Asterleeds town gate square has been registered.
Now we're ready to go.
Let's head out of town and look for clues to memory.

When I left Asterleeds, I found a wide open plain.
This is the "Asteria Plains.
Various plants, ores, etc. were found, and the ruins of Bapharia were scattered about.
Monsters also appear ahead. Be on your guard.
Head for the "Cliff Ruins" where you met Feste.
There you may find clues to your memory.

I got into a fight with Goblins in "Cliff Ruins".
Some of the monsters seem to act in packs. Be careful when you fight them from now on.
This is where I met Feste. This is where I woke up.
Will I find anything?

Where I woke up. found 'Imagine'. It is said to be a crystal that combines the will of the engram and the creature.
The crystals are said to be a combination of engrams and the will of the creature.
It has various powers, but does not seem to be a clue to memory. There was nothing else to be found.
There was nothing else to be found.
As I was about to go outside, I thought I heard a strange voice. But there was no one there.
But there was no one there.
When I left the ruins, I met an Adventurer named "Jake. He spoke in a lighthearted manner, but was known as "Jake" in Asterleaze.
He was a well-known figure in Asterleeds and seemed to be in charge of organizing Adventurers.
Jake said, "If you are going to be an adventurer, you must be a good one.
Jake promised to introduce me to the Pioneer Bureau if I would become an Adventurer.
Jake promised to introduce me to the Pioneer Bureau if I wanted to become an adventurer. Feste also suggested that I sign up as an Adventurer.
He said, "You may be concerned about your memory, but first you need money! He said. ......
However, I knew I would be in trouble if I didn't have a job. We should go to the settlement office and see what Jake has to say.
Jake's story.

To become an Adventurer, you must clear several tasks.
The first task is to Hunt "Land Fox".
Be on your guard. Be prepared for the challenge.

We have successfully Hunt Land Fox.
I'll report back to Murie as soon as I can.

The second task is to explore the Lakerid Mine.
It is an old tunnel in Roaring Sea Meadow.
Monsters have inhabited the tunnels since they were closed, but the danger is not that great.
If you reach the deepest part of the tunnel, you have passed the assignment.

Lakerid Mine can be accessed through "star vein holes".
The tunnels are located in various places and are said to lead to various places such as ruins and caves.
When you find one, remember its location.

I had never heard of such a powerful enemy - Ogre - appearing in the Lakerid Mine.
According to Feste, it was "too tough for a novice Adventurer.
Even so, we managed to defeat it.
With this, we should be able to move on to the next test subject.

The presence of an ogre in the "Lakerid Mine" was apparently unexpected, even for the Pioneer Bureau.
Muiry reported the discovery and thanked us for the Hunt.
However, the examination is another story. I had to clear the next assignment.
The third assignment is to 'learn about Craft.
The first thing to do is to make Weapons. Let's go talk to Huovi, who is at the Craftsman Square, and ask him about the details.

Huovi taught me the necessary steps for Crafting Weapons.
He told us that if we obtained the recipe, gathered the necessary materials, and used the "rolling ball kneading ritual," we would be able to obtain a weapon.
In the registration test, the assignment was to actually craft a Weapon.
Gather the materials and use the "Rolling Ball Crafting Ritual" to craft a Weapon from the "Adventures" series.

Weapons from the "Adventures" series have been Crafted.
Now I just need to get Huovi to check it out.

The third assignment was also successfully completed.
The last assignment was "Crafting an Enhanced Imagine".
It seems that Poirier of the Imagine Research Institute is in charge of this assignment.
The laboratory is located just outside of the Pioneering Station. Let's visit there right away.

Poirier gave me more details about the assignment.
Enhance Imagines are "equipable Imagines" that enhance the physical abilities of the wearer.
They are as important to Adventurers as weapons.
Crafting Enhance Imagine also requires a recipe and materials.
The one to be Crafted for the assignment is "E-Uri Piglet".
Gather the materials and ask the Imagine Research Institute to Craft it for you.

I was able to Craft "E-Uri Piglet" from Enhance Imagine.
I'll have Poirier check it out.

Jake and I are going on a monster hunt.
I heard that a boar-like beast appeared in Dragon Claw Valley. It is said to be "a bit of a bad guy" that is tougher than ordinary monsters.
The Reward for this is good.
Let's meet up with Jake in front of the Dragon Claw Valley.

I met up with Jake in front of Dragon Claw Valley.
Let's explore "Dragon Claw Valley" with Feste and Jake and Hunt the monsters.

The "husband buys you a drink" was a trick by Jake to get Feste to have a drink. ......
After a brief argument, Feste brought up the subject of Merluof's remaining word, "The Visitor.
The husband told him that it might have something to do with the Bapharia religion. However, he didn't seem to know the details.
There is a huge Bapharia temple in Asterleeds.
I decided to ask about "The Visitor" there.

Do not speak of "the visitors" without knowing who they are," the priest told me.
The Priest reminded me that I could not ask for more details.
However, a girl who was looking at me from behind a pillar told me that I could find out something if I went to Minsterhorn.
The mysterious girl disappeared as soon as I took my eyes off her.
There were no other memories or clues to the "visitor.
Let's follow the girl's words and go to Minsterhorn.

I met a woman named Milene in Minsterhorn.
She told me that her mentor, a Priest named Walkin, knew a lot about "The Visitor".
However, Walkin went to the "Giant Tower Ruins" to investigate and never returned.
Milene, who was worried about him, asked him to help her.
Let's go to "Giant Tower Ruins" to look for Walkin.

The Pillar of Divinity is said to be the place where the founder of the Bapharian faith descended from, and is the most sacred place of the Bapharian faith.
Therefore, the Gatekeeper turned him away, saying, "You can't enter without permission.
Feste tried to coax and scold him, but it seemed that what could not be allowed could not be allowed.
We wondered if we could get a permit from somewhere.
Let's have a strategy meeting at Larpal.

In Larpal, I heard a rumor about a Bapharia pilgrimage group.
The city of Berkmar was recently destroyed by a strange monster.
A Bapharia pilgrimage group is visiting the city to mourn its victims.
Some of the pilgrims are of high rank, such as Priestesses and oracle priestesses.
Perhaps they could get permission to enter the "Pillar of Divinity.
Let's go to Berkmahal and meet the pilgrims.

In Berkmar, I met again with the mysterious girl I had met in the temple of Asterleeds.
When I told her that I wanted to enter the "Pillar of Divinity", she somehow gave me a permit.
Who in the world is she?
Before I could ask her, she walked away again.
Anyway, I got the permit. Let's show it to the Gatekeeper of "Pillar of Divinity.

The Gatekeeper seemed surprised when I showed him the permit that the girl from the pilgrim group had given me.
It seemed that the permit was genuine. After some hesitation, the Gatekeeper finally let us through.
Now we could enter the "Pillar of Divinity.
Let's go to the top floor in search of clues about the "visitors.

Tyris and his team have a device called "Omnistron" that searches for Avaritia.
However, it seems that it was damaged in the battle at "Pillar of Divinity".
They asked me to collect parts to repair it.
Let's go to "Machine Trace Valley" and get the parts.

Tyris and his team contacted the child of Omnistron.
It seems to be able to send not only voice but also text. This is amazing.
Tyris seems to be tense because he is Aerinse's only escort.
Aerinse also told me that she was sorry.
Until he gets used to it, it would be better for us to give him a little.

Let's meet up with the girls who have gone ahead of us at Rietze in Montenol Valley.

Upon arriving in Rietze, I ran into a group of Bapharia pilgrims.
There they found the girl who had given them a permit to enter the "Pillar of Divinity".
She was Einlein, the "oracle priestess".
We did not know why she had lent her power to us. Before we could call out to her, the pilgrim group had gone.
A series of dragon tribe attacks and the appearance of monsters have caused anxiety among the people. Avaritia is one of them.
I hope that liberating Avaritia with Aerinse and others will lead to peace. ......
For now, let's follow Omnistron's reaction.
The everyday and the extraordinary in a piece of paper
The recipient of the gift is

The next Avaritia to be liberated seems to be in the Silent City, which is controlled by the Bapharia cult.
Feste is quite enthusiastic about the possibility of finding treasure at the ruins, which are rarely frequented by Adventurers.
The story is supposed to be about a world crisis. ......

The next Avaritia to be liberated seems to be in the desert.
There is a barrier on the road leading to the desert. We must pass through there.

Ahead of us is the Evergreen Desert.
It's the setting for a new adventure.
Omnistron's response is out toward the desert.
First, let's proceed toward the city of Salamzat.

I came to the Temple of Bapharia in Salamzat for information on Avaritia.
The omnistron cannot be used now that the light-colored wind is blowing.
Aerinse said that the temple might be able to tell us about Avaritia. ......

Charlotte, the diva we met at the entrance to the desert.
It seems that the Zilwet Traveling Troupe, to which she belongs, is about to begin a performance.
Aerinse is looking forward to it, and Einlein wants to see it too.
I also have an appointment with Charlotte. Let's all go see the performance together.

Carvain and Charlotte were to retire to a hiding place.
Apart from that, Einlein had a request to make.
It was something that was difficult to talk about in the temple.

We met up with Aerinse and the others and talked about Carvain, Charlotte, Einlein and Joerg.
Aerinse and Tyris also had something on their minds.
They said it was about an old man, but they seemed to be at a loss as to what to say to him.

Elektra has something to ask of me.
Is it something to do with the Bapharia cult?

After crossing the scorching desert, we finally arrived at Salamzart Oasis.
The best way to relieve the fatigue of the long journey is to eat something sweet.
Tyris decided to serve a cake for Aerinse.

Tyris says he has some personal business to finish.
'Something fishy about that .......'
Intuiting that something interesting must be about to happen, Feste decides to follow her.

Joerg was in trouble.
He had lost a piece of paper that he had tucked into his notebook when he ran away from the insects.
It was a personal diary and not much was written in it, he said. ......

I need you to find my missing congregation."
Elektra's strangely formal request reveals an unknown side of her.

Veronica, Deputy Commander of the Knights of the Duchy of Bernhart.
Will the day come when her feelings reach that person in her heart? ......

Avaritia response to Omnistron!
But it was not a target to be released.
Should it be defeated or not? ......What decision did Tyris make?

Aerinse and Tyris visit Asterleeds for the first time.
Everything they see is new to them, and they enjoy a brief respite.

Hunt against Avaritia in the Silent City.
When we arrived, a young man was fighting Avaritia first.
Despite his efforts, he collapsed and was unable to move.
They decide to carry the young man to a place where he can rest while Aerinse performs the liberation ceremony.
The garrison of the Bapharia cult must be close by. Let's go there.

Hunt for Avaritia in "Akatsuki's Insect Fortress".
This is another Avaritia to be liberated. Aerinse advances to perform the liberation ceremony.
At that time, Avaritia, which should have fallen down, got up with a terrifying vitality.
Then, a figure descended from overhead. With a thrust of his spear, Avaritia sank to the ground.
Dunkirk, the leader of the Knights of the Duchy of Bernhart, appeared. He seemed to have been investigating these ruins with his subordinates in tow.
After Dunkirk and his men left, Aerinse safely liberated Avaritia.
Let's go back to Einlein for the time being and tell him not to worry about Avaritia.

On the way home, Tyris was a little slow on his feet, as if something was bothering him. Was something wrong?

Charlotte went home to her troupe mates.
Carvain also left, as he was going to join his friends.
I feel tired after all that has happened.
Let's take a break at the rest stop.

Joerg was the son of Dunkirk, the Knight Commander of the Duchy of Bernhart.
He was a childhood friend of Einlein and Carvain, and they are still close friends.
Joerg is personally investigating something, and Einrain and his friends are helping him with it.
However, he was successfully sidetracked as to the details of his research. Maybe it's something he doesn't want us to know too much about.
Einlein's business is done. Joerg seems to be staying here and asked me to take Einrain back to Salamzaat.

A mysterious old man told an old story about a Priest.
The Priest had a woman whom he admired. Alicia's blessing" were the words that she used to say.
The Priest searched for the "Sandwind Flower" that the woman had asked for. In the process, he was surrounded by a dazzling light and landed in a strange land where people, culture, and everything else was different.
And then, he said, a long month passed.
At the old man's request, Tyris held the "Flower of the Sand Wind" and smiled awkwardly. The old man, seeing this, nodded his head in satisfaction.
He then said he would deliver the thank-you to the rest stop, and quietly left.

Hunt for Avaritia in Whispering Cliffs.
With the light winds subsiding and the omnistrons now available, it was determined that this was the Avaritia that should be released.
While Feste was getting Elektra's attention, Aerinse was able to complete the liberation ceremony as well.
However, there was suddenly a disturbing shadow.
Dragon King Voldigen appeared, and Elektra also revealed her true form as the dragon tribe Frelbe.
She infiltrated the Bapharia cult under Voldigen's orders. She then monitored Aerinse's activation of the biological engram through the release of Avaritia.
Voldigen's goal is to feed on that Aerinse and gain power. Aerinse's condition and whereabouts were all being kept in the loop by Frelbe.

The companions fell helplessly before the overwhelming power of Voldigen.
Aerinse was captured and about to be eaten.
The Imagine seed that Carvain had given her shone brightly, and a beautiful singing voice began to flow out.
Voldigen suffered from the singing and flew away into the Sky.
Before she had time to catch her breath, Frelbe, who had turned into a giant dragon, attacked her.
After a mortal struggle, she disappeared into the deep valley floor.
She was no longer in sight.

The threat of the dragon tribe had passed.
Feste, Aerinse, and Tyris somehow managed to survive.

The recovered young man introduced himself as Carvain.
He seemed to have been investigating something in "Silent City." He seemed to have expected Avaritia to be there, but how did he know?
Carvain gave him an Imagine seed, which he said was his most treasured possession, as a thank-you for his help.
As soon as I received it, a strange scene flashed in my mind.

Somewhere, a boy was wielding a sword.
Someone was watching over him.

I suddenly realized that Carvain had already left. I'll ask him about the details the next time I see him.
Aerinse and Tyris had also finished liberating Avaritia and joined the group.
Our next destination was the desert. The next destination was the desert, where "Salamzat" was located.

We are now able to pass through the barrier safely.
Now I can go to Salamzat.
I am looking forward to experiencing a different place and a different culture.

The team arrived at Salamzat.
At the same time, a glowing wind occurred that disrupted the flow of engrams. The omnistron was temporarily disabled and Avaritia's whereabouts were unknown.
Then Aerinse suggested that they go to the Bapharia temple. At the temple, he said, he might be able to get some information about Avaritia.

Einlein, too, seemed concerned about Avaritia.
He was relieved to hear that there was nothing to worry about.
A cheer went up from the plaza. It seems that Charlotte's traveling troupe of entertainers is about to begin their performance.
I have an appointment with Charlotte, and Aerinse is leaning forward happily.
It would be good to take a break once in a while.

I had a strange dream.

--I dreamed that I was in a forest and someone was holding me up.
I could not move, and I heard a voice crying out, "Mother," over and over.
"Mother," he cried over and over again.

When I opened my eyes, I saw a bag of small money under my pillow.
Then I saw Charlotte's back as she walked away.
Feste had noticed, too, and together they followed Charlotte to the entrance of the city.
Charlotte seemed quite concerned that she had been attacked by an Armed Group. She was trying to disappear on her own, fearing that her troupe mates might get involved.
Then Carvain and Einlein approached him.
They were friends, and Einlein said that he really wanted to help Charlotte. Furthermore, Carvain was a member of the Knights of the Duchy of Bernhart, making him the perfect person to protect Charlotte.
Carvain said that he had to go into hiding for some reason. He also offered to shelter Charlotte there.
Charlotte agreed and left the city with Carvain. Now she would not have to worry.
Meanwhile, Einlein asked me to do something for her. Let's hear what she has to say once she settles down.

Back in Salamzaat, Elektra caught Einlein in a very angry mood.
It seems that Einlein will somehow cover up what happened to Joerg. The matter is probably over for the time being.

A young man came to the rest area and said that he was asked by an old man.
The old man had passed away.
As a thank-you gift, he delivered a commemorative coin of the Bapharia religion. It was quite old, probably from the time of the founder.
There is no way to know for sure what really happened to the old man.
The Flower of the Sand and Wind" shattered in Tyris's hands and disappeared.
It was as if it was bidding farewell to the end of a long journey.

It has been a long day.
Many things have happened and too much to think about.
Let's rest now.
I'll look for answers later.

At the customs office, we were asked to present a guarantor.
This seems to be a new requirement, as no one knew of any guarantor.
It seems that Dunkirk, the leader of the Knights of the Duchy of Bernhart, which has political unrest, is visiting Salamzat and is therefore under heightened vigilance.
The condition for a guarantor is that the guarantor must have lived in Asterleeds for at least 10 years.
According to Feste, the Coin Owner has been running the store since before that time, so there is no problem as a guarantor.
We have to turn back, but we have no choice.
Let's head to Asterleeds.

The Coin Owner almost mistook me for a guarantor of his debt.
Words like "new servant" and "senior servant" were uttered by Aerinse and Tyris, and the husband's eyes became colder and colder. ......
Anyway, he agreed to be a guarantor with conditions.
My husband has been using an Imagine seed to contact his brother. It has been broken and he wants to repair it.
He needs a few special materials, so he wants me to collect them.

I was able to collect the materials to repair the Imagine seed.
Let's deliver them to Coin Owner.

Coin Owner took on the role of guarantor.
He also prepared a certificate for me.
Now I should be able to pass through the barrier.

Just as they entered the desert, they found a group of Travellers fleeing from the monsters.
In order to help them escape, the Girl had used them as bait to attract the monsters.
I immediately went to help them and came across an unusually strong Bapharia priestess. She, too, had heard the story and had come looking for the Girl who had taken the bait.
The priestess is taking care of the monsters in the area.
Let's find the Girl while we can.

I was able to save a Girl who was being chased by a monster.
Her name is Charlotte. She is a diva of a troupe of traveling entertainers who are scheduled to perform in Salamzat.
She said she was confident in her foot speed, but she was reckless.
Aerinse's eyes lit up when she heard that she was a traveling performer. Charlotte invited her to the performance and promised to go see it.
Charlotte left with her friends who came to pick her up.
I am glad to hear that she is safe. Let's go to Salamzat, too.

In the temple was Elektra, a priestess I met in the desert.
She is the guardian of Einrain, the oracle priestess. However, Einrain had wandered off and they were looking for her.
According to Aerinse, "the oracle priestess has detailed information about Avaritia.
I decided to help Elektra in her search for Einlein.

Einlein was playing with children in the back of the settlement office.
He was telling them a story about the "beast" that once destroyed the world, but it seemed to bore them.
Instead, Feste sang a beautiful song.
The tone of the song attracted not only the children but also Einlein.
While Feste was teaching the song, Elektra arrived.
She asked Einrain about Avaritia, who was being brought back to her, and he told her that she was in "Akatsuki's Insect Fortress.
Why did Aerinse think that the oracle priestess knew where Avaritia was?
I did not get a clear answer from her.

Charlotte's stage began to a roar of cheers.
But it soon turned into screams.
An unidentified Armed Group suddenly attacked her.
Charlotte ran out of town. The Armed Group chased after her.
No need to be told by Einlein.
We must go to help Charlotte immediately.

It was Carvain, whom she had met in the Silent City, who protected Charlotte when she was cornered.
Working together, they kicked out the Armed Group and were able to save Charlotte.
Tyris, who had rescued the injured, also joined them. The town has regained its calm.
However, Charlotte had no idea that her life had been threatened.
On his way back to Salamzat, Carvain dropped an old button. He said it was a clue left behind by the group that once took his mother.
Carvain may have a complicated story to tell.

Einlein wanted to meet a friend of hers in secret, even from Elektra and her friends. She wanted to ask them to escort her there.
Let's take her to the Hermit's Fountain in the Evergreen Desert.

There was no sign of Einlein's friend Joerg at the Hermit's Fountain.
Instead, his handkerchief, footprints, and insect carcasses were left behind.
Joerg is not very fond of insects, and even the smallest ones make his blood run cold. And if he were attacked by a large insect monster, his life might be in danger.
Let's hurry up and look for Joerg.

An insect monster appeared at the end of Joerg's tracks.
I wonder if Joerg is safe.

After Hunt, a young man emerged from the shadows.
He was Joerg. He had escaped from the insects and was safe. Joerg seemed to be a bit strong to Einrain who was worried about him.
It would not do to be attacked by insects again after standing here and talking.
Let's go back to the safe tent.

A certain old man in Salamzat says that he may have been chronoleptic.
If so, we can't just leave him alone.
Let's talk to the old man just to be sure.

The Old Drunk mumbled "Alicia bless you ......" in the Old Drunk.
Definitely the activation word for the Chronogate.
When the old man saw Tyris, he suddenly became conscious and clear. He was so surprised that he seemed unable to speak.
The old man had asked him to deliver "The Flower of the Sand Wind. Apparently, it was someone's favorite flower.
He promised to tell us everything he knew if we gave it to him.
The "Flower of the Sandwind" is something that the desert winds produce by chance, and we don't even know where it is.
Let's ask Einrain to help us here. The Bapharia cult's information network might be able to catch something.

I was able to hear from Einlein and Elektra.
They said that a few years ago, "The Flower of the Sand Wind" was found at the "Boruomu Ruins".

Deep in the "Boruomu Ruins" I obtained a "Flower of the Sand Wind".
Its beauty caught the eyes of Aerinse and Tyris. Both of them were so moved that their bodies trembled.
I wonder if that old man also sought this out of beauty.
Let's deliver "The Flower of the Sand Wind" to the old man in Salamzat.

Hunt for Avaritia was requested by Elektra.
Avaritia appeared along the pilgrimage route, and they concluded that it would be better to Hunt it than to go around it.
Einrain told Elektra about the Hunt for Avaritia in "Akatsuki's Insect Fortress," which led to the request.
Feste was also persuaded with the words, "I'll give you a reward.
Anyway, they could not leave Avaritia alone.
Let's meet up with Elektra and head for Hunt for Avaritia.

Avaritia has appeared at the "Whispering Cliffs," she said.
Elektra spoke up and said that the Order should originally take responsibility for Avaritia.
She said that the Bapharia cult has sealed Avaritia in a sacred place and has been collecting and using a huge amount of engrams from it.
I could not hide my surprise at the unexpected truth. Elektra immediately minced words, but it was too late.
It seems that Aerinse also knew about the connection between the Bapharia cult and Avaritia. Come to think of it, Avaritia was also sealed in the Chronogate of "Pillar of Divinity.
Aerinse is going to tell us what happened when he finishes this Avaritia case.
For now, let's go to "Whispering Cliffs" and Hunt Avaritia.
Talakua fruit (usu. a grapefruit, a pomelo, etc.)

He survived a fierce battle not only with Avaritia, but also with Dragon King Voldigen and the dragon tribe Frelbe.
Now we need some rest.

Aerinse has been taken away to the future by Bachelard.
According to the voice from the Imagine Seed, Aerinse will be used in some "plan".
Aerinse's life is in danger.
Let's go to the future with Tyris and rescue Aerinse.

Tyris was taken into the avaritia shell, chronoleptically leaped and disappeared.
He must be somewhere in this time period.
It seems that Merluof knows where the Avalitya Shell appears.
In the future, he said that he would be in Asterleeds if he were in this time period. ......

Avalitya Shell is believed to be in the "Blessed Temple", an important center of the Bapharia cult.
The only way to get there is to use the transporter in the temple in Asterleeds.
We would have no choice but to ask permission to use it.
Let's talk to the high Priest in the temple.

Ryugerio has some kind of request for us.
There are a lot of things we want to know about what has happened since Avaritia Shell appeared at the cathedral.
Let's hear what he has to say first.

The Troupe Leader and his wife of the traveling troupe Zilwet were worried about Charlotte, whom they had loved like their own child.
Let's try to respond to their wishes and find a way to get in touch with Charlotte.

A Demi-Dragon appears in Asteria Plains!
Adventurers are suddenly agog with excitement.
Some are snickering, hoping to make a name for themselves.
Others shied away, believing it was too much for them.
But the one who dashed past them all was that boy.

The sudden order to return given to Tyris and Aerinse.
At least a side trip to make memories of this era. ......
What is their last wish?

Before returning to the future, Aerinse revealed the truth to me.
She is the princess of the divine tribe of Bapharia.
The "gods" who once built an advanced civilization and created human beings still live beyond the Sky.
They have given instructions to the Bapharia cult through an oracle to retrieve the engram from Avaritia, which is sealed in the holy land.
However, the resulting distortion caused by Avaritia has accumulated and led to the destruction of the planet.
Aerinse wanted to release this cause and effect and seek a new future.
Even though it was only for a short time, Aerinse told me that the trip with them had been "fun.
Hearing this, there was a glimmer in Feste's eyes.

At the Chronogate on the top floor, Bachelard was waiting for them.
His face was familiar. It was the man he had seen in his dream - the man who had taken the crying boy's mother away.
Bachelard took one look at me and attacked without saying a word. Tyris was also hit, and Aerinse was put into a coma.
Bachelard then took only Aerinse with him and chronoleptically leaped.

Left behind, a voice from Imagine Seed was heard.
'Save Aerinse,' it said, 'she is being used for the 'plan.'
The voice did not answer the question. However, Aerinse cannot be left alone as she is.
The way to the future, Charlotte says, is open to her.
Let's hurry to the Khartoum ruins to meet her.

In addition to Charlotte and Carvain, Einlein and Joerg were at the Khartoum site.
The oracle had been given to Einlein and he was waiting here.
Charlotte, in accordance with the oracle, entrusted a pendant to him.
Inside was a chronogram of surprisingly high purity, much to Tyris' surprise. She said that even if all of us did the chronoleap, it would still contain more than enough power.
With this, we could rescue Aerinse.
He thanked Charlotte and the others, and they were off to the future from the "Pillar of Divinity.

The laboratory where the avalitia shell was installed could be seen.
Already in the final stage, a black haze began to extend from the Avalitya shell to Aerinse at Bachelard's signal.
Tyris jumped in and rescued Aerinse just in time. However, this time Tyris was caught in the avalitia shell.
An alarm went off, and Bachelard gave the order, but the movement of Avalitya Shell did not stop.
Unable to reach Tyris's outstretched hand, she was swallowed up by the Avalitia Shell.
The next moment, the Avaritia Shell seemed to glow with a dazzling light, and then vanished without a trace.

According to Bachelard, the Avalitya Shell had jumped back to its own time - 1,000 years ago. Moreover, the effect of the jump had disrupted space-time, making it impossible to chronoleap and pursue them.
In the middle of the impasse, Merluof arrived with Frelbe. He understood the whole situation and said, "I will make it possible for you to chronoleap.
Half-convinced, I went to the chronogate and found that the space-time was indeed stable. This would make chrono-leap possible.
Bachelard proposed a partnership with the goal of capturing Avaritia Shell.
Aerinse was emotionally reluctant to nod, but she gave priority to saving Tyris and accepted the proposal. Bachelard's support, including the preparation of the chronogram, was essential to the rescue of Tyris.
Leaving Frelbe to monitor the situation, he and Aerinse again went on a chronoleap.
The destination was their own time.
They must find Avaritia Shell and Tyris, who were supposed to be there.

We interviewed people in town and found Merluof.
About six months ago, Merluof sensed an unusual occurrence of engrams in the "Blessed Temple" under St. Bapharia Island.
It was probably caused by avaritia shells.
According to Aerinse, the Avalitia Shell jumps through time and space without using a chronogram. It is thought that this caused the time period to shift and history to move within half a year.
The Blessed Temple is an important center of the Bapharia religion. The only way to get there is through the temple in Asterleeds.
I don't know if they will give us permission, but let's go to the temple anyway.

Avalitia Shell was found in the innermost part of the Blessed Temple.
Einlein has set up wards to contain the avaritia shell. It will no longer be able to move around on its own.
Tyris is half buried in the avaritia shell, sleeping. They have not yet completely fused.
However, at some point, the avaritia shell will wake up and take in Tyris.
Before that happens, we must find a way to separate Tyris.
Otherwise, the world will face a future of destruction.

If there were no way to rescue Tyris--
If we cannot avoid the future of destruction--what will we do?

I search for the words to answer Feste's question.
What will I find at the end of this world, this journey--?

A person named Bachelard contacted Tyris. It seems that he had sent instructions to Tyris from 1000 years in the future.
After reporting the Voldigen incident, Bachelard was concerned for Aerinse's safety and gave the order to return to the future.
The liberation of Avaritia was also suspended in order to prioritize Aerinse's safety.
As a "last request," Tyris asked me to take them back to the "Pillar of Divinity.
Once they return to the future, we will never see each other again.
It is sad to say goodbye to them, but it is ...... inevitable.

We are ready to leap into the future.
Let's head for the Chronogate of "Pillar of Divinity".

Tyris told me about Aerinse and Bachelard.
Bachelard and Tyris belong to a thought group called "Zorukishia" within the Bapharia theosophical clan. Tyris's original mission was to escort and monitor Aerinse.
However, as he got to know Aerinse's personality, Tyris was drawn to her and came to serve her wholeheartedly.
Tyris' desire to help Aerinse is genuine. I am sure that Aerinse knows this.

After the chronoleap, we have finally arrived at the future, 1000 years in the future.
Let's hurry to Aerinse.

A thousand years later, in the "Pillar of Divinity," I met again with Frelbe of the dragon tribe.
She has lost her memory of this time period, and is said to be serving Aerinse with Tyris.
Frelbe was also on her way to the research facility to save Aerinse, who had been kidnapped. When I accompanied her, Frelbe told me about Bachelard's plan.
It was the "Avaritia Shell Project.
The plan was to fuse Aerinse with a special "Avaritia Shell" to control other Avaritia.
Of course, there were many objections, and in the end it was decided that Aerinse would liberate Avaritia.
However, even this was Bachelard's intention. As a result of the release of Avaritia and the activation of the biological engram, Aerinse had become more easily fused with the Avaritia shell.
Even now, the fusion of Aerinse and Avalitia Shell is underway.
We must reach the research facility as soon as possible and stop the plan.

I reached the first floor of the "Pillar of Divinity. However, the entrance to the research facility is closed.
Then, the image of Bachelard was projected.
Bachelard is trying to proceed with the Avalitya Shell project. It was not to control Avaritia.
The real purpose is to destroy an overdeveloped civilization, the "Beast of the Planet.
The whole point of the Avalitya Shell project was to control the beast, which is not a fairy tale but a real thing in the imaginary world.
Bachelard tells Aerinse that the sacrifice of one person is unavoidable in order to protect the planet and civilization. However, Tyris does not accept this and clearly states that he wants to save Aerinse.
The soldiers sent by Bachelard are taken care of by Frelbe. He says that the research facility can be reached by following the tracks where she once went on a rampage.
We are one step closer to saving Aerinse.

There seems to be no noticeable change in Asterleeds.
It seems like a lie that we went to the future.
Let's go to the Coin Pavilion to gather some information.

When I arrived at Coin Owner, he was just leaving.
Jake is taking care of his absence, but I heard that there was talk of closing the restaurant for a while. I asked him about it, and he told me that he was surprised to hear from Jake.
When I inquired about it, Jake told me a surprising story.
King Bernhart was assassinated during an attack by the dragon tribe. Moreover, the main culprit was Carvain, and he was listed on the wanted list.
The king was supposedly recovering from an illness. It is not true that he was assassinated during the attack by the dragon tribe, and of course Carvain would never have assassinated him.
However, there is a discrepancy with the history we know.
After all, there may have been some influence by the avaritia shell.
We should immediately seek out Merluof and ask him about the whereabouts of Avalitya Shell.

At the temple, Priest Ryugerio was waiting for me.
He easily gave me permission to use the transporter and told me to go to the "Blessed Temple".
Accepting Einlein's oracle, he said that the Bapharia cult would cooperate fully.
I heard that Einrain is also in the "Blessed Temple. Let's go there and hear more details.

In the Blessed Temple, Einlein had set up a ward.
He said it was to put the "angel of God" who appeared six months ago to sleep.
The wards should have been placed closer to the angel, but the monster inside is preventing the angel from getting close to it.
The oracle Accepted by Einlein was to "eliminate the monster and suppress the angel's anger. Hearing this, Aerinse guessed that Bachelard had given instructions to the Order in the form of an oracle.
In any case, there is no doubt that Tyris and Avaritia Shell are here.
In order to save Tyris, we need to go to the innermost part of the building.
